---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Privacy Policy — BugReel',
  description: 'BugReel privacy policy. Learn how we handle data, what we collect, and how self-hosting keeps your recordings on your own server.',
  url: 'https://bugreel.io/privacy',
  breadcrumb: {
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://bugreel.io' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Privacy Policy', item: 'https://bugreel.io/privacy' },
    ],
  },
};
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — BugReel"
  description="BugReel privacy policy. Learn how we handle data, what we collect, and how self-hosting keeps your recordings on your own server."
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="legal-header section-sm">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
        <span>Privacy Policy</span>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section-sm">
    <div class="container legal-container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <section>
          <h2>Overview</h2>
          <p>
            BugReel is a self-hosted bug reporting tool. This means your screen recordings,
            transcriptions, bug reports, and all associated data are stored on <strong>your own server</strong>,
            not ours. We do not have access to your recordings or bug reports.
          </p>
          <p>
            This privacy policy covers two things: the BugReel software (self-hosted) and this
            marketing website (bugreel.io).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>What We Collect</h2>

          <h3>BugReel Software (Self-Hosted)</h3>
          <p>
            When you run BugReel on your own server, we collect <strong>nothing</strong>. All data
            remains on your infrastructure. The only external communication is between your server
            and the AI provider you configure (e.g., OpenAI) for transcription and analysis.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you activate a license key, a one-time validation request is sent to our licensing
            server. This request contains only the license key and your server's domain. No
            recording data, user data, or bug report content is transmitted.
          </p>

          <h3>This Website (bugreel.io)</h3>
          <p>
            For this landing site, we collect minimal, anonymous analytics data to understand
            page views and traffic sources. We do not collect personal information, email
            addresses, or create user accounts on this site.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>How We Use Data</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>License validation:</strong> To verify your license key is valid and active.</li>
            <li><strong>Website analytics:</strong> To understand which pages are visited and improve our documentation.</li>
            <li><strong>Support requests:</strong> If you contact us via email, we use your message to provide support.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Data Storage</h2>
          <p>
            BugReel is self-hosted by design. Your recordings, transcriptions, screenshots, bug
            report cards, and user accounts are stored exclusively on your server. You have full
            control over data retention, backups, and deletion.
          </p>
          <p>
            We do not operate any cloud service that stores your bug report data. There is no
            "BugReel cloud" that your data passes through.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>
            The BugReel software integrates with third-party services that <strong>you</strong> configure:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>OpenAI (or compatible API):</strong> Audio transcription and AI analysis are
              processed by the AI provider you specify in your configuration. Review your AI
              provider's privacy policy for how they handle API data.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Issue trackers (Jira, Linear, GitHub, YouTrack):</strong> When you export a
              bug report, data is sent to the tracker you selected, using credentials you provide.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Webhooks:</strong> If configured, bug report data is sent to the webhook URL
              you specify.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            None of these integrations send data to BugReel. All communication is directly between
            your server and the third-party service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            This website uses minimal cookies for basic functionality (e.g., remembering consent
            preferences). We do not use advertising cookies or cross-site tracking.
          </p>
          <p>
            The self-hosted BugReel application uses session cookies for authentication. These
            cookies are stored on your domain and controlled by your server.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Your Rights</h2>
          <p>
            Since BugReel is self-hosted, you have direct control over all your data. You can view,
            export, modify, or delete any data at any time through your server's database and file
            system.
          </p>
          <p>
            For any data we may hold (e.g., support emails, license records), you have the right to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Request access to your data</li>
            <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent at any time</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about this privacy policy or how your data is handled,
            contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@bugreel.io">hello@bugreel.io</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .legal-header {
    padding-top: 32px;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
  }

  .breadcrumb span:last-child {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .legal-container {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .legal-container h1 {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .legal-content section {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-bottom: 8px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .legal-content h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .legal-content li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .legal-content a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .legal-content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
